README
(latest updated : July, 7. 2009 by Sanghoun Song)

KRG: Korean Resource Grammar (HPSG for Korean)
 - by Jong-Bok Kim and Jaehyung Yang, 2008
 - by Francis Bond and Sanghoun Song, 2009


1) This is a release of the Korean Resource Grammar (KRG).

2) This is a linux version of the KRG. This grammar requires PET (for parsing) or LKB (Linguistic Knowledge Builder; for parsing or generation) for operation. 

3) See license.txt for conditions.

4) You can download the latest version of KRG at http://sites.google.com/site/krgproject/ or get from the LOGON subversion (http://wiki.delph-in.net/moin/LogonInstallation). 

5) You can get all papers that cover Korean Resource Grammar at http://sites.google.com/site/krgproject/

